stylometry: Fixed cost gives you that constraint. You must add in the factor to your total target cell. Set covering models are important because you have a large data set withing. A fixed cost example would be the producing and shipping of the envelopes problem we did in class with the company's mailing list. There were fixed costs of the envelopes and mailing for each item going out. You must consider this in the target cell because you can't just rely on your other changing cells. It isn't labeled constraint but it is just an added factor.
